      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n1-ptr" id="PJA04d032n1">1</a>
      
   <p>Not found.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n2-ptr" id="PJA04d032n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Maj. Gen. Lord Hugh Percy (17421817) of the 5th Regiment of Fusiliers (Worthington C. Ford, comp., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">British Officers Serving in the American Revolution, 17741784</span>, Brooklyn, 1897; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Leslie Stephen and Sidney Lee, eds., &lt;i&gt;The Dictionary of National Biography&lt;/i&gt;, New York and London, 18851900; 63 vols. plus supplements. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">DNB</span></span>).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n3-ptr" id="PJA04d032n3">3</a>
      
   <p>That is, instead of a telescope, he used a magnifying glass (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Oxford English Dictionary&lt;/i&gt;, Oxford, 1933; 12 vols. and supplement. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">OED</span></span>).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n4-ptr" id="PJA04d032n4">4</a>
      
   <p>19 March was a Tuesday, but his writing June is inexplicable.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n5-ptr" id="PJA04d032n5">5</a>
      
   <p>That is, the British.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n6-ptr" id="PJA04d032n6">6</a>
      
   <p>Maj. Gen. James Grant (17201806) of the 55th Regiment of Foot (Ford, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">British Officers</span>; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Leslie Stephen and Sidney Lee, eds., &lt;i&gt;The Dictionary of National Biography&lt;/i&gt;, New York and London, 18851900; 63 vols. plus supplements. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">DNB</span></span>).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n7-ptr" id="PJA04d032n7">7</a>
      
   <p>Sullivan continues the banter regarding <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s house that he began in his letter to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-03-02-0193" class="document">21 Dec. 1775</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d032n8-ptr" id="PJA04d032n8">8</a>
      
   <p>John Stark (17281822) of New Hampshire, a veteran of the French and Indian War, who, despite the recommendation of Sullivan and conspicuous service to the American cause, remained at the rank of colonel. His failure to win promotion caused him to resign his commission in March 1777. When Burgoyne invaded New York, the New Hampshire General Court made Stark a brigadier general. Starks victory in the Battle of Bennington in Aug. 1777 won him the rank of brigadier general in the Continental Army (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Allen Johnson and Dumas Malone, eds., &lt;i&gt;Dictionary of American Biography&lt;/i&gt;, New York, 19281936; 20 vols. plus index and supplements. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">DAB</span></span>).</p>

     </div>
